-- Pakistan Halts Supplies to Nato Afghan Mission After Three Soldiers Killed
-- B y   A n w a r   S h a k i r
-- 2010-09-30T06:33:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/pakistan-halts-supplies-to-nato-afghan-mission-after-three-soldiers-killed.html
Pakistan blocked supplies for NATO
troops fighting in Afghanistan after an airstrike killed three
Pakistani security personnel, Umair Khan, a local government
official in Khyber Agency said by telephone.  Two soldiers were also injured in the strike, Kamal Khan,
deputy district officer for the Kurrum Agency said by telephone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
